	<entry>
		<title>By: Rob Earl</title>
		<link rel="alternate" href="/index.php/webdev/serverprogramming/automated-monitoring-of-remote-vnc-serve/#comment-3164" type="text/html" />

		<author>
			<name>Rob Earl</name>
			
		</author>

		<id>/index.php/2010/08/automated-monitoring-of-remote-vnc-serve/#comment-3164</id>
		<updated>2010-08-30T13:52:12Z</updated>
		<published>2010-08-30T13:52:12Z</published>
		<content type="html" xml:base="/index.php/webdev/serverprogramming/automated-monitoring-of-remote-vnc-serve/#comment-3164"><![CDATA[<p>Thanks for the welcome!</p>
<p>For anyone looking to use this for a similar purpose as me you could go further and use Image::Imlib2->query_pixel(0,0) and compare it to the desktop colour to test for browser crashes.</p>
<p>Maybe even use Image::Imlib2->load to open the previous screenshot then compare it to the new one to test for browser lockups.</p>
<p>You&#8217;d then be able to setup email notifications for most faults.</p>
]]></content>
